:: The Weight of Ash (K) {"position":"5000,200","size":"100,100"}
Your partner, Yuri, is due home soon. Your children, Ella and Toby, were playing a loud, joyful game nearby. In the midst of that comforting ordinary world, you had a small, familiar item you always kept close—a token of your children's innocent joy.


:: The Weight of Ash (Y) {"position":"3200,100","size":"100,100"}
You have just left the market with a wrapped loaf of bread and two miserable looking potatoes, the only things you managed to trade for fixing an old radio. //Food is becoming more difficult to come by//, you think to yourself. //There has to be something else I can do or fix to trade for more food.// These thoughts haunt you as you make your way home alone, cautious of anyone that holds their glance at you for too long.

As you approach your house, you notice the sweet scent of baking apples. Apple pie? //That woman has done it again!// You wonder what it is that Katya, your wife, had to trade in order to get her hands on apples. Before opening the door and heading inside you notice the hammock you have been weaving for the kids over the past few weeks. If you take a little bit of time now, you think you could finish it before going inside for dinner.

[[Finish weaving the hammock]] or  [[Go inside for dinner]]


