:: Watch them pass by {"position":"2300,200","size":"100,100"}
You watch the armored trucks get closer and closer. 

They fire their guns at you, blowing a hole the size of a fist through the child in your arms. You want to scream, but find it hard to process anything that just happened. Taking a step forward, you find yourself falling over the limp body of Pyotr. The world goes silent.

Information is not registering to you. You attempt to move but find it harder and harder.

You've been shot.

(text-colour:(hsl:0,0.8039,0.5,0.8))[You bleed out on the soggy ground crumpled over the corpse of your son.]

[[Try again]]


